!! <<f-i map>> [[Leaflet maps plugin]]
the <$link to="$:/plugins/sycom/leaflet"><<f-i download>> Leaflet maps plugin</$link> will embed leaflet maps in your tiddlywiki with the `<$leafmap />` widget. See the [[Michel Strogoff|Michel Strogoff from the sky]] (map below) or [[included doc]] examples to learn more.

The plugins also brings the <<f-i map-pin>> [[geoLocationWidget]] which creates a button to collect the current geolocation of your browser. But it may be used independently if you do not need the plugin...

<$leafmap tileControl height='210px' tile='natgeo' places='{"filter":"[tag[Michel Strogoff from the sky]]"}' cluster='5' />
//the [[Michel Strogoff from the sky]] example to see what can be done with it. see also plugin embedded [[example|$:/plugins/sycom/leaflet/example]]//

!! <<f-i eye>> [[Google analytics plugin|G-Analytics plugin]]
the <$link to="$:/plugins/sycom/g-analytics"> <<f-i download>> Google analytics plugin</$link> is a fork of the official one you will find in the TiddlyWiki plugin library. It enables internal individual tiddlers tracking and is //Do Not Track// compliant.

!! <<f-i feather>> [[Feather icons plugin]]
the <$link to="$:/plugins/sycom/feather-icons"><<f-i download>> Feather icons plugin</$link> offers an icon library alternative to the Font Awesome one. It's pretty lightweight and elegant.

!! <<f-i rss>> Atom feed plugin
the <$link to="$:/plugins/sycom/atom-feed"><<f-i download>> Atom feed plugin</$link> will create an <a rel="alternate" href="atom.xml" target="_blank">atom.xml</a> file alongside your wiki. Helpful for people who whish follow your work.

!! <<f-i globe>> [[i18n macro]]
the <$link to="$:/ext/modules/macros/i18n-macro.js"><<f-i download>> i18n macro</$link> will help you to have a multilingual wiki if you wish without hacking internal //language + lingo// system in TiddlyWiki...
